T8	Evidence 344 759	A comparison of the primary structure of the phosphopeptides with that of EF-2 showed that all 4 phosphopeptides originated from one region of EF-2 located near the N-terminus that contains 3 threonine residues: Thr-53, Thr-56, Thr-58. A direct estimation of localization of radioactive phosphate in the phosphopeptides demonstrated that all the enumerated threonine residues in EF-2 can be phosphorylated in vitro.
